<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1922&amp;p=16466#p16466"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Quick q about snes_ntsc settings]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1922&amp;p=16466#p16466"><![CDATA[
There's no good way to counteract the overall dimming effect of scanline darkening beyond increasing the monitor's contrast control. The full range of each color component is already being used, so the only way to make things brighter would be to multiply by a factor &gt; 1.0 and clamp things that hit maximum value, resulting in visual degradation.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Aug 22, 2006 2:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
